On 13 Feb 1992 04:02:42 -0800, merlin@neuro.usc.edu (merlin) said:
> Curiously, no common system security book, article, or even a government
> orange book seems to either mention or give a solution for this problem.

Actually, the orange book does address this problem, in the object reuse
requirement. This requirement effectively says that whenever an object is
created, there should no way to read any information from a prior use.

